  "mixStrategy": "This sleep reggae arrangement uses 3 tracks carefully separated by frequency to create a warm, enveloping bed of sound. The chord progression is I (G) \u2192 IV (C) \u2192 I (G) \u2192 V (D) \u2192 IV (C), repeating in long 10-second phrases. BASS (Electric Bass, 100-300Hz): Anchors everything with extremely slow, sustained root notes (G2, C2, D2) in the low register (MIDI 31-43). Notes are long (4-8s) with gentle velocity (30-45), providing a deep, warm foundation. Uses root-5th movement with whole notes and dotted halves. CHORDS (Organ, 300Hz-2kHz): Plays the classic reggae offbeat skank but slowed to a dreamlike pace. Chord voicings sit in MIDI 60-72 range. In sleep mode, these are extremely soft (vel 25-40), sustained pad-like washes on the upbeats with long sustains (4-8s), creating harmonic warmth without rhythmic urgency. Triads voiced as G-B-D, C-E-G, D-F#-A. MELODY (Nylon Guitar, 1-5kHz): Sparse, vocal-like phrases in MIDI 60-72 range. Plays only chord tones on strong beats with gentle passing tones. Very few notes (one every 2-4 seconds), long sustains (4-8s), creating a lullaby quality. Velocity 30-45. Energy arc: Segments 1-2 (0-15s) start very quiet with bass and sparse organ, melody enters gently. Segments 3-4 (15-30s) reach modest peak with all three tracks softly interacting. Segments 5-6 (30-45s) gradually fade, melody thins, bass sustains longer, organ drops out. All tracks change chords together at the same moments. NO drums per sleep mode. The result is a warm, dark, slow-motion reggae lullaby.",
